body:
Here is my proposed solution for @MechCoder's question `What are you planning to do with the previous PR? In other words, what are the use-cases of exposing SystemML datastructures to the not-so-advanced user?` (see https://github.com/apache/incubator-systemml/pull/204):

We stick with `start ... eval` construct for now as it has simplest logic and focus on the design of built-in functions (i.e. to make `full` API compatible with NumPy). When we are relatively happy with the design, we push this PR in as WIP and mention in our doc that `start ... eval` will be removed in future. The advanced push-down logic and lazy data structures will be implemented in Scala DSL. Once this DSL is part of master, we replace [addPyDMLStmt and related functions](https://github.com/apache/incubator-systemml/pull/197/files#diff-2c4346a06f8454b330603d8a0dee33b7R37) with calls to Scala lazy structures. With this, we can then remove `start ... eval` logic :) 

@dusenberrymw @frreiss @mboehm7 @bertholdreinwald  Please feel free to provide your suggestions.
